summary.purpose: Provides four coloured car SVG icon generator functions (red, yellow, green, gray) conforming to the VehicleSvg signature for use as map markers and menu icons.
summary.problem_solved: Supplies the car vehicle type's state-specific icon variants so that map and menu components can reflect real-time ignition and speed state visually.

internal.why_used: Imports the VehicleSvg function type used to type the exported icon functions.

exports.name: redCarIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a red car SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: yellowCarIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a yellow car SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: greenCarIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a green car SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: grayCarIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a gray car SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

symbols.name: redCarIcon
symbols.description_one_line: Returns a red car SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

params.name: width
params.description: Width attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: height
params.description: Height attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: siteColor
params.description: Fill colour used for site-specific colour accents within the SVG paths.

params.name: className
params.description: CSS class name applied to the SVG element.

params.name: viewBoxFor
params.description: Context identifier ('map_icon' or 'menu_icon') that may alter viewBox or path rendering.

returns.description: A React SVG element representing a red car icon at the specified dimensions.

details.what_it_does: Generates a detailed car SVG icon filled with a red colour scheme. Accepts all VehicleSvg parameters so it can be composed by getVehiclesIcon and generateVehicleIconForMenu. The red colour indicates the vehicle's ignition is off (parked/stopped).

minimal_correct.title: Render a red car icon
minimal_correct.code:
import { redCarIcon } from 'akeyless-assets-commons';

const icon = redCarIcon('30', '30', '#FF0000', 'newIconCar', 'map_icon');
